<dl id="n10084d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10084d">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10084d"> 84(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> stand to gain</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">EASTER, 1916. Remarkable Letter From Rev James Kelly, P.P. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> But this was no gombeen bargain that Christ was promising the double-dealing Jews&mdash;it was simply telling them they would lose nothing but <mark>stood to gain</mark> everything by following the straight path of this very fundamental principle&mdash;in other words, that honesty was the best policy. Even to that treble dealing schemer and political outcast, Lloyd George, this principle has made lip service appeal of late. <small> <a name="CT26apr24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CT26apr24"><cite title="source">Connacht Tribune</cite></a> (26 April 1924) 5/4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
